                <note rend="inline" type="source">660f.116Auto/46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Einstein</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-02T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">02, February 1929—noon</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 2—9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Legation’s despatch No. 1689, December 6, 1928.<note n="56" xml:id="d718fn56"
                        >Not printed.</note> Foreign Office note informs Legation confidentially
                    that American motor contingent will be increased from 800 to 1500 cars. Kindly
                    refrain from publicity.<note n="57" xml:id="d718fn57">American automobile
                        interests were given permission to receive this information in confidence;
                        telegram 17, Feb. 28, 1929, from the Chargé in Czechoslovakia to the
                        Secretary of State (file No. 660f.116 Auto/53).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Einstein</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
